President Trump met with 24 CEOs from major manufacturing companies to discuss bringing manufacturing jobs back to the United States. He emphasized his commitment to creating high-wage jobs and delivering on his campaign promises. The President also mentioned specific companies, such as Intel, Ford, GM, Walmart, Amgen, Amazon, Fiat, and Carrier, that have announced significant new investments in the U.S. He expressed his intention to negotiate better trade deals and create a level playing field for American businesses. The CEOs in attendance represented nearly $1 trillion in sales and 2 million employees.